cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper discusses the properties and behavior of word embeddings generated by neural network methods, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves probabilistic modeling and mathematical descriptions, which suggest that it could also fit into cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the linear relationships between embeddings, which could relate to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) subcategories.
